The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Anand in joint lead after win
                                                   Anand in joint lead after win
                      
	Nice: After drawing with Vladimir Kramnik in the opening blindfold game, world champion Viswanathan Anand defeated the Russian in their rapid match in the first round of the Amber Blindfold and Rapid chess tournament here.         
	Anand emerged as a joint leader in the rapid and combined standings after beating Kramnik.         
	In the rapid, the Indian is joined by Armenias Levon Aronian while in the combined standings it is a five-way lead between Anand, Aronian, Veselin Topalov of Bulgaria and Ukrainians Vassily Ivanchuk and Sergey Karjakin.         
	It was in the return game that the Indian ace proved superior after Kramnik slipped from a position of strength.         
	Shakhriyar Mamedyarov of Azerbaijan and Alexander Morozevich of Russia signed peace in both their games to reach a 1-1 tie. It was a long encounter in a Nimzowitsch Defence by Morozevich in the blindfold game. (PTI)                                                                                                                       
